Create a Google Apps Script function that generates charts from lab data in Google Sheets.

Requirements:
- Use the currently active sheet (do not depend on sheet name)
- Automatically detect the data range (rows and columns)
- Read the header row and identify columns using keywords like:
  "absorbance", "concentration", "time", "temperature"
- If matching columns are not found, fallback to the first two numeric columns

Charts to generate:
1. Histogram for the detected Y-axis column (e.g., Absorbance)
2. Scatter plot:
   - X-axis: detected X column (e.g., Concentration or Time)
   - Y-axis: detected Y column (e.g., Absorbance)
   - Add linear trendline and display R² value

Additional features:
- Remove any existing charts before creating new ones
- Automatically position charts below the dataset
- Use dynamic chart titles based on column headers
- Add Logger messages for debugging
- Validate that sufficient data exists before plotting

Return only clean and well-commented Apps Script code.
